<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870619-0121 </DOCNO><HL> Alcoa Offers to Buy Back$150 Million of Debentures</HL><DD> 06/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AABUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Aluminum Co. of America offered to buy $150 million of its 12 1/4% sinking fund debentures due 2012.    The aluminum producer said it will pay $1,105 for each $1,000 face amount of debentures, plus accrued interest, until 5 p.m. EDT June 30.    The buyback is part of the company's program to reduce its average debt cost, Alcoa said. The offer is being co-managed by Merrill Lynch Capital Markets and Salomon Brothers Inc. </TEXT></DOC>